Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.33,0:01:27.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星距离太阳5亿英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is half a billion miles from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.05,0:01:30.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的结构复杂的星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A giant sphere of intrigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.75,0:01:35.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个旋转着的气态星球看上去象一幅艺术家的画作 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This turning ball of gas may look like an artist's rendering,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.04,0:01:37.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而却是真实的物体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.04,0:01:44.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星具有太阳系里最奇特的气象模式 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter has the most exotic weather patterns we had ever seen in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:01:48.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星有84%的氢 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is 84% hydrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:50.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,差不多14%的氦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and almost 14% helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:53.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这两个是宇宙里最轻和最多的元素 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the two lightest and most abundant elements in the Universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:56.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,组成它庞大的身躯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rolled into a mammoth mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.95,0:01:59.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这家伙的直径是地球的11倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This thing is eleven times the diameter of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.23,0:02:05.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以轻松地将1000个地球塞进木星里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you could take a thousand Earths and stuffed them inside Jupiter comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.05,0:02:11.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星真的是太阳系里的霸主 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter really is the lord of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.45,0:02:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,知道吗 行星的大约70%左右的物质在木星里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You know, about 70% of the mass in all the planets is in Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.39,0:02:19.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你谈论行星 木星是团伙里最大的孩子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you talking about planets, Jupiter is the big boy in the block and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:20.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它真的称雄称霸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it really does rule the roost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.28,0:02:25.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星是太阳系里最大的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is the largest planet in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.05,0:02:27.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肉眼能明显地看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Visible to the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.99,0:02:31.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星上一天只有9.9小时长 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A day is only 9.9 hours long.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.01,0:02:35.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕太阳转一圈需要11.86年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it takes 11.86 years to orbit the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.37,0:02:40.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,150磅重的人在木星上会重达350磅 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A 150 pound person would weight 350 pounds on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.42,0:02:50.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有氨 硫磺和水组成的雷雨云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are thunder clouds made of ammonia, sulfur and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.15,0:02:56.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探索木星是美国宇航局迄今最大胆的使命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Exploring Jupiter would be NASA's most daring mission to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:59.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个不友善的地方 温度极端 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a hostile place, with temperature extremes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.42,0:03:01.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从冰箱到火炉 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from fridging to firing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.71,0:03:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的电磁辐射很强 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its electromagnetic radiation is intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:12.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会顷刻杀死来访者 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could kill a traveler to the planet in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.53,0:03:16.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要厚重的铅的保护 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would need heavy lead protection
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:19.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得在地面上举步艰难 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's very difficult to lift off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.40,0:03:22.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上人们到木星去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we have some difficult engineering challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:24.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在工程上是个艰难的挑战 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to actually bring human beings to the planet Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:27.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在木星登陆是..不会发生的 \NA landing on Jupiter is… not going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.45,0:03:31.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星本身是个非常气态的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter itself is a very gassy planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:33.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是由气体组成的 所以你…\NIt's made of gas. So you…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.22,0:03:36.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会有固体的地表站立和四处走动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would not have a solid surface on which to land and walk around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:40.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只会不断下降穿过云层然后最终坠毁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would just keep descending through the clouds and then be eventually crashed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.80,0:03:42.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠着木星大气层的压力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the pressure of Jupiter's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:45.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就使得人们到木星旅行具有挑战 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That make a human trip to Jupiter quite a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.89,0:03:51.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们能去那里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what if we could go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.35,0:03:57.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安德鲁·英格索尔博士行星的权威 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Doctor Andrew Ingersoll is an authority on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:03:59.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他带我们做一次环游 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He takes us for a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.24,0:04:03.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你需要一个特别的气球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You need a special kind of balloon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.84,0:04:06.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为木星的大气层是氢气 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the Jupiter's atmosphere is hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:11.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢是最轻的气体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hydrogen is the lightest gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:14.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,载人气球会下沉 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A human balloon would sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:20.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以唯一的情况是在寒冷的氢大气层里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the only thing that'll flow in a cold hydrogen atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.33,0:04:22.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用热的氢气漂流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is hot hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.07,0:04:25.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此需要加热气球里的氢气 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so you need a hot-air hydrogen balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.84,0:04:32.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的10年里 美国宇航局研发着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the past ten years, NASA has been developing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.81,0:04:36.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超长期限的气球 用于机械人探测 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ultra-long duration balloons, for robotic exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:41.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正如我们知道的那样  加热氢气是件棘手的事情 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as we all know, heating hydrogen is a tricky thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:56.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但究竟这个巨头是如何诞生的仍然是个谜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But just how this behemoth was born, is a puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.62,0:05:02.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的形成关联着行星最大的谜团 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The formation of Jupiter is the greatest mystery associated with the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.81,0:05:07.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人认为木星可能是不合格的恒星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some believe Jupiter may have been a failed star.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:10.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就象太阳一样有着合适的成分 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like the Sun, it had the right ingredients,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:11.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氢和氦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hydrogen and helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:15.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是没有足够的质量形成内部核融化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But not enough mass to create the internal pressure and temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.27,0:05:17.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所需要的压力和温度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}necessary to have nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.26,0:05:20.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它变成了行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, it became a planet instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:27.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,理论上那里有银河系的星云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The theory is that there was this cloud in the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:29.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和太阳的成分一样的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that had the same composition of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:37.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它自己的引力下塌缩 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it collapsed under its own gravity and some stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.45,0:05:38.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些东西还是留了下来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.05,0:05:40.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留下的部分成为了行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that stuff became the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:46.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多数变成了木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the majority of that stuff became Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.81,0:05:49.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其余的当然跑进了太阳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the rest, of course, went into the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:51.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有几个细小的残留物 就象地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there were a couple of little tiny leftovers, like Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.73,0:05:57.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星旋转的气体吸引了轻的元素 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's spinning gasses attracted light elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.26,0:06:01.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这过程中成长得越来越大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and overtime grew bigger and bigger in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:08.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎就象牡蛎 围绕着沙粒一层一层制作着珍珠 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Almost like an oyster, creating layers around the grain of sand to make a pearl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.56,0:06:12.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有被木星摄取的气体和固体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What gasses and solids Jupiter didn't ingest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:14.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被加速抛入太空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it sped out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.67,0:06:21.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以木星就象在校园里的大哥哥 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So Jupiter is like the big brother in the schoolyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.10,0:06:24.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保护着你免受威胁你生存的浩劫的欺凌 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}protecting you from bullies that might wreak havoc on your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:37.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我倾向于认为它更象宇宙飞盘家伙 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I tend to think of it as more of the cosmic Frisbee guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:44.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它把物体抛出太空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's grabbing things out of space
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.36,0:06:46.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也把物体折腾回来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's also tossing them back out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.37,0:06:50.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它处死来自太阳系内部的物体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It ends up keeping those objects from the inner solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.83,0:06:53.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里有地球 火星和金星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where Earth and Mars and Venus are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:55.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过清理一些碎片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By cleaning some of the debris up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:58.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把一些抛出去 把一些射到太阳里去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}kicking some of it out, shooting some of it into the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.88,0:07:00.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样碎片就会永远消失 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where it would be lost forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.33,0:07:03.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星清理出一条道路让其它行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter cleaned out a path that the other planets could
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.40,0:07:06.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保持一些安静 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exist in some sort of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:09.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞盘现象的如此优势 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So dominant is this Frisbee phenomenon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.12,0:07:13.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球可以将生存归功于木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth may owe its very existence to Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.28,0:07:17.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它影响到慧星 甚至一些流星和小行星的路线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It influences the courses of comets and even some meteors and asteroids,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.13,0:07:20.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此通过施加在近地物体上的作用 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that over the NEOs the effect of Jupiter is there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.57,0:07:22.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帮助照顾太阳系附近的物体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}helps takes care what comes near the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.71,0:07:25.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这么看来木星的存在真的是地球产生生命的原因之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So really the presence of Jupiter may be one reason why we have life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.91,0:07:29.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过打击大量的慧星 使地球成为可居住之地 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and habitability and be able to have the Earth nice environment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:31.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有着美好环境 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}instead of getting pummeled by so many comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.61,0:07:37.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有比木星在1994年七月的七天里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is no greater proof of Jupiter's power play
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:42.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发的力量更有力的证据了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than what happened during the seven day period in July of 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.91,0:07:48.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗名叫苏梅克列维9号的彗星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A comet called Shoemaker-Levy 9
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.61,0:07:51.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向着木星高速行进 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}barreled toward Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:57.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在木星的影响下一去不复返 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once under Jupiter's influence there was no going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.40,0:08:03.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体和气体星球发生了碰撞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A missile was on a crash course with a ball of gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:10.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的引力是如此的巨大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's gravitational pull was so great
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.38,0:08:13.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把慧星拉成碎片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it broke the comet into small pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.58,0:08:15.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一次一个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that came in one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:22.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些碎片以每秒37英里的速度攻击木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These pieces assaulted the planet at a speed of 37 miles per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.57,0:08:27.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当物体以超音速行进时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you have a missile going at supersonic speeds
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会感到震动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you get a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:39.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到物体产生的云从地面上腾起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can see sort of clouds of material being jetted up from beneath where it landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:46.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个火球在与木星大气层的碰撞中升起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the fire balls generated by the collision with Jupiter's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.59,0:08:49.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高达1800英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flared 1,800 miles in the space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:57.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少可以这么说 在地球的范围内 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Had Earth been in the projectile sights
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:02.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种打击将是灾难性的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the effects of such a smash up would have been catastrophic to say the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.49,0:09:08.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,类似的打击已经灭绝了恐龙 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Similar to the event that wiped out the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:13.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些碎片打击释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energies that were released in those fragments hitting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.60,0:09:17.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样要十倍或二十倍于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was larger than anywhere of ten or twenty times
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:21.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全球所有武器的能量总和 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more powerful than the entire world arsenal of bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:23.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把木星拿走 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take Jupiter out of the picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:25.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把这颗慧星放到太阳系里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bring this giant comet into the inner solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:26.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会到哪里去？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where would it have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.01,0:09:28.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.31,0:09:29.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Might have crashed into Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.31,0:09:36.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那颗慧星撞进地球  这里周围的一切将会完全不一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that comet had crashed into Earth, things would be a lot different around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:47.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,专家们认为打击木星的慧星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The experts believe that comet strikes on Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.71,0:09:51.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能比那些撞击地球的物体大8000倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be 8,000 times more frequent that those on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:53.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大大感谢飞盘的作用 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thanks to the Frisbee effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.08,0:10:02.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两败俱伤 因为木星没有价值系统 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it cut both ways because Jupiter has no value system,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.38,0:10:06.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它看到一个犯错的慧星就可能吸引并吞噬它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it sees an erring comet it may attract it and swallow it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.98,0:10:08.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是投掷的地方可以是任意的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But where it flings is anyone's guess
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:12.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以犯错误的慧星可以被投向地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so erring comets can be flung in towards Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.29,0:10:13.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也可以投进太阳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can be flung into the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.80,0:10:15.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也可以投出太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can be flung out of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.31,0:10:24.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前提是行星拒绝一些太空垃圾挡住自己的道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a reason the planet rejects some of the space junk heading its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.11,0:10:29.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星是太阳系里最大的行星 有着最大的引力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter being the biggest object in the solar system has the most gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:32.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此其它物体会逐个逃离 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so other objects literally flees,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:35.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有自己的行进轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they have their own trajectory flying by, are bent
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:39.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里它们通常会以加速度奔向木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from where it would be towards Jupiter and usually with an acceleration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.15,0:10:46.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而加速度有时会将它正好被撵出来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that acceleration can cause it sometimes to just be ejected completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.95,0:10:53.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上没有飞盘投掷者能和木星投掷力相媲美 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No earthly Frisbee thrower can match Jupiter's flinging force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:03.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道这比子弹要快的多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is much faster than any bullet ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:06.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其反作用力的速度达每秒30英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It rejects things at a rate of 30 miles per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:17.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星奇观的是难以探测的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's wonders are hard to fathom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:20.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迷惑人类已经几个世纪了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've captivated men for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.21,0:11:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,史前人们认识到它在恒星之间运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Prehistoric humans realized that it was moving among the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.82,0:11:28.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是他们欣赏的行星之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it was one of the planets that they appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:31.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星是上帝之王 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter was the king of the Gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:33.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟在罗马神话里是这样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after all, in Roman mythology.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.30,0:11:39.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且圣经也曾提到过木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there may be a biblical reference to Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.90,0:11:42.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打从五岁开始 我记得人们说过:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ever since I was like five years old I remember people:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.31,0:11:44.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"噢 那是颗伯利恒之星 "\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Oh, that was the star of Bethlehem!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.61,0:11:49.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不论是否真的 我们无法知道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And whether or not it really was, obviously we have no way of knowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.21,0:11:53.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而还不清楚关于那颗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's not clear whether the star that was talked about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.33,0:11:56.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是单一的星体还是一个天体的天文联盟 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a single star or whether they met an astronomical alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:11:59.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们没有真正了解 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of objects in the sky, we don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:03.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,按照科学述语它是联合体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's known as conjunction in scientific terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:06.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,按照对木星和金星的研究 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to researches Jupiter and Venus
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.64,0:12:11.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公元前3年8月作为大的类星体发布 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}did appear as one large star-like object in August 3 B.C.,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:14.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会在东方的夜空看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and would had been visible in eastern night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.58,0:12:21.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而现代天文学之父伽利略 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was Galileo, the father of modern astronomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:25.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首次记载了看到的木星系统 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who made the first recorded sighting of the Jupiter system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.51,0:12:31.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在1610年早期 望远镜发明后仅仅18个月 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the early days of 1610, only about 18 months after the telescope was invented,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.63,0:12:33.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他用自己的望远镜看到了木星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he got his own telescope and he was on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:44.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在1665年木星最迷人的面貌被揭开 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1665 Jupiter's most fascinating feature was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:48.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它那巨大的红眼实际上是巨大的风暴之眼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its giant "red eye" was actually the eye of an enormous storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全不同于地球上的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike any experienced on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.45,0:12:56.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这在300年前引起一场狂热 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This one has raged for at least 300 hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.91,0:13:05.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个天象搅乱了气象学家的梦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This weather disturbance is a meteorologist's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.21,0:13:09.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星巨大的红斑实在是大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's Great Red Spot, is truly huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:13.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以把地球展开放进去  甚至还无法盖住这个红斑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can take Earth and flare it out and then wouldn't even really cover the Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:16.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个风暴是太阳系里最大的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This storm is the hugest storm in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.33,0:13:18.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,感觉大约宽12000英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And just to give a feeling about it, it's about 12,000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.33,0:13:22.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球却只有8000英里宽 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the Earth is only 8,000 miles wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.93,0:13:27.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风围绕其边缘快速流动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the winds blow quiet fast around the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:31.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而其中心很平静 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's calm in the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:33.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它…它不象飓风那样\NIt's… It's not like a hurricane
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:37.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一个眼并且中心有狂风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has an eye and very fast turbulent winds in the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:39.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红斑相当平静 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Red Spot is rather calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:43.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你有个气球 可以很舒适的飞行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you're in a balloon, it might be a pleasant ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.43,0:13:47.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要你能避开小规模的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As long as you avoided the small scale stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.35,0:13:50.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,诸如雷暴和吵闹的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like the thunderstorms and the turbulent places.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:54.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使你跑的很快 它也相当平静 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though you'd be going very fast it might be quite calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.55,0:13:59.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以快达每小时350英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fast as in 350 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.15,0:14:06.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上曾经记录到每小时175英里的风速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fastest wind ever recorded here on Earth was 175 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:12.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那是象地球上一样的风暴吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But is it an Earth-like storm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.75,0:14:15.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它吸纳了周围紊乱的云 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a giant collection of clouds roiling around,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:17.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雷电轰鸣…\Nlightning going on…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.05,0:14:23.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此我们只能模拟它的情景 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we can only model an imagine of what kind of precipitation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.45,0:14:28.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各种气体凝结成蒸汽存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but condensation in the form of condensed vapor of various gasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.45,0:14:32.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个著名的红斑是个高压系统 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This famous Red Spot is a high pressure system
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:35.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够在10天里完全翻转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can take 10 days to complete a rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:38.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实向后的飓风称为反气旋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Truly a backwards hurricane is called an anticyclone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:42.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是对那些旋转方向向后的典型飓风的命名 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's the name for those circles backwards on the direction of a typical hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.17,0:14:53.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不仅仅是好奇的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's not the only curious thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.25,0:14:56.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正如我们知道的飓风 需要水才能形成 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hurricanes, as we know them, need water in order to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.66,0:15:05.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而红斑里没有水的动力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no water engine in the Red Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.47,0:15:10.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个永不停顿的天气系统有点象别的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This never-ending weather system is feeding on something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.26,0:15:12.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:22.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星大红斑象不停的飓风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's Great Red Spot is something like a non-stop hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:27.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是庞大的风暴 全部是狂风和雷电 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a colossal storm, complete with violent wind and lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:31.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴猎人喜欢跟着它跑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Storm chasers would love to go running after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:35.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,路易斯维耳大学的蒂姆·道林博士\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dr. Tim Dowling of the University of Louisville
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:38.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热衷于地球上相似的现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is in the hot for similar phenomena here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.30,0:15:47.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红斑是… 认为它象是个庞大的极端…\NThe Red Spot is…  Think of it as a huge extreme…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:15:51.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,***陆地或***巨大的鸡蛋形状 一个巨大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}***lands or*** egg shape of mass, such as an enormous thing that sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.98,0:15:55.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,平静下来的气流 把它压进温度较高的内部 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}quiets down the fluid and the presses it down into the hotter interior
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:57.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以不会有雷击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you don't get thunderstrokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.62,0:16:03.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果进入到红斑的边缘 特别是在西北部 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if you go on the edge of the Red Spot, specially north-west,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:07.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会看到木星上最可怕的雷暴 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you get some of the most horrific thunderstorms you're gonna find on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.34,0:16:13.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红斑没有一个眼 它不是用水来驱动的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Spot doesn't have an eye and it isn't fueled by water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.61,0:16:16.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从它形成以来就没有海洋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no ocean over which it forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.35,0:16:20.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么是什么使它保持周而复始的运行的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What then keeps it going and going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.34,0:16:24.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我总是把它比作我看到的…象\NI've always liken it in my own view as… like a mini volcano
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:27.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星里的一座迷你火山 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inside of Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.04,0:16:30.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是座大气火山 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Actually an atmospheric volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:36.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贝恩斯博士认为是木星里的热加热了气体上升 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dr. Baines believes that warmer gasses rise from heat, deep within the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:39.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气体试图逃逸时产生了旋涡 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While trying to escape they create a vortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.43,0:16:45.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以基于这些理由 我相信那里正好有额外的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, for some reason I believe there's extra energy right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.38,0:16:48.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这不是理论 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's just a theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.18,0:16:51.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学对这个问题以及其它一直没有答案 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science is left without answers to that question and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.29,0:16:56.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当前理论上还无法解释红斑为什么如此完美 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Current theories cannot quite explain why the Spot is so well-formed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.08,0:16:59.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么会存在一颗行星上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and why it stays in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.14,0:17:04.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家多年研究的积累更多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The plot thickened over the years as scientists learnt even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:06.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它变得更扑朔迷离 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It became a deeper mystery because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.53,0:17:09.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为围绕着红斑平静运行的一切 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}instead of everything just sort of smooth going around the Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:11.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看上去是混乱的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we saw there's turbulence and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.62,0:17:15.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有小的物体每天在来回 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there were smaller scale structures that come and go every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.89,0:17:21.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是混乱无序的 然而红斑控制着它们的生存 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it was chaotic and triggering and yet the Red Spot just existed and stayed hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.28,0:17:25.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星风暴不仅仅限定在大红斑里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's storms aren't limited to the Great Red Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.99,0:17:30.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,云厚厚地遮盖三层 遮盖着行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cloud decks three layers thick hover and cover the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.01,0:17:36.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你在木星的大气层里 你会听到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were inside the atmosphere of Jupiter you would hear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:38.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常响的雷鸣 事实上雷声传播\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very loud thunders. In fact we have thunders
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:42.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,的速度居然比地球上快4倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually which travel four times faster on Jupiter than it does on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:44.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每小时大约3000英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's about 3,000 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.70,0:17:48.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,落下的雨是地球上的两倍快 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So rain falls twice as fast on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:52.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正电荷被推向云层的顶部 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The charge separation that pulls the positive charges to the top of the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:56.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,负电荷被推向云层底部 这在木星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the negative charges to the bottom of the clouds is twice as efficient
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.38,0:18:00.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是独一无二的快两倍 这是因为下的鱼要快两倍的缘故 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on Jupiter for that reason alone, because the rain is falling so much faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:04.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在木星上看到的塔状积雨云比地球的高三倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Towers of cumulous convection that you see on Jupiter are three times taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.78,0:18:09.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高达30英里 而地球上的只有6-7英里高 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They go up 30 miles whereas on Earth they go up 6 or 7 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.43,0:18:22.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在大红斑里不可能存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be impossible to survive within the Great Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.77,0:18:25.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那有每小时350英里的风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with its 350 mile-an-hour winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.69,0:18:32.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为比较 飓风威尔玛 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By comparison, hurricane Wilma,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.10,0:18:35.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前世界上有记录的最高风速 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which had the highest recorded winds of any earthly storm,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.80,0:18:40.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2005年严创尤卡坦半岛 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slammed into the Yucatan peninsula in 2005 with barely a breath,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.39,0:18:44.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风速达到每小时175英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}175 mile-an-hour blasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.59,0:18:49.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的天气是简单的 木星的天气是复杂的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our weather is simple, Jupiter's is complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.42,0:18:52.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在木星上基本上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now on Jupiter you just basically have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.49,0:18:56.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一个风暴接着一个风暴 一个接着一个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one storm system sort of stacked on another stacked on another
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:18:57.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伴随着许许多多的摩擦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with lots and lots of rub.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:19:00.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,基本上那些风暴是其自然状态 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Basically these are the storms in their natural state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.11,0:19:07.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些风暴在木星上无情地移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These storms move relentlessly within Jupiter's other distinct feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:12.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,凶猛的气流围绕木星不断流动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}streams of fierce jets that continually circle the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:17.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家还只是开始了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists are only beginning to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:19.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴是什么和从哪里来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what they are and where they come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.66,0:19:27.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这有朝东的流动的物质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a massive eastward flow of material
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.72,0:19:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意味着…\Nand that means…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.63,0:19:34.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物质以每秒一个半足球场的速度流动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the material's flowing more than one and a half football fields per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.46,0:19:38.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那真的是在流动 你不会想呆在那的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's really moving, you don't want to be in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:44.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变着宽度方向的29地带和其它地区 从那往外扩展 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}29 other belts and zones of varying width extend outwards from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.79,0:19:48.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给了木星特有的面貌 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are what give Jupiter its characteristic appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:52.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们交叉移动 有时向东 有时向西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They move in alternating directions, some eastward, some westward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.69,0:19:58.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高纬度的要比近赤道的规模要小得多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're much smaller scale the high latitude jets than the equatorial one,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:02.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对照一下地球上的距离 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as far as in comparison to Earth these are massive,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.11,0:20:07.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超高速 高速的风刚好反过来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}super-fast high-speed winds and yet they're just going back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.48,0:20:12.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这和行星自转的速度有关 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet's rotation rate has something to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.65,0:20:16.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星产生大量的能量是因为它确实的运转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter generates a lot of energy because it really moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.12,0:20:20.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以非常自然的旋转使得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the very nature of the spinning causes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.41,0:20:25.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星不仅仅产生一个风暴 还会产生更多的风暴 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter to not just have one jet stream but many jet streams
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.37,0:20:28.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕着行星的相对应的方向 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}going in opposite directions along the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.07,0:20:30.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你会看到这些地方 所以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so you can see these zones, so what you have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.63,0:20:34.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会有地球基本气象模式的夸张写照 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is an exaggerated version of Earth's basic weather pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:41.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表面云产生壮观的气旋会分区碰头 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spectacular swirls are created in surface clouds where the zones meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:47.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这被认为是能量最后带动这一带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's believed that the energy ultimately powering this belt phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.01,0:20:50.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剧烈的热从深处出来的现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes from intense heat deep within.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.21,0:20:54.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不同于我们每天所看到的现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not unlike something we see every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.15,0:20:59.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,买一个水壶装上水放在炉子上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Buy a boiler pot of water on a stove, it'll start bubbling
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.13,0:21:01.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会开始从壶底往上冒泡 努力挣脱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and bubbles come out from the bottom and try to get out trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.94,0:21:04.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面的水流不断循环 所以…\Ncirculate that water that currents around, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.33,0:21:06.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样的事情也发生在木星内 气体和液体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}same thing inside Jupiter, we have gases and liquids down there
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.01,0:21:08.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下降下去 热释放出来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are trying to get the heat out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.27,0:21:14.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有个基本问题 基本的物理原理去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are basic questions, basic pieces of physics to go after
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.08,0:21:17.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,解释大规模的气流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to explain the massive jets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.99,0:21:21.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够解释这个问题？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shouldn't we be able to explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.35,0:21:25.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球就有一个主要的气流往东移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth has just one primary jet stream, it moves eastward,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.56,0:21:29.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而另外一个主要的气流往西移动 所谓的信风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and another major flow that blows westward, the trade winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.29,0:21:34.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星上的气流的能量是地球的三倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Triple that power and you've got the jet streams of Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:38.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一切都不同于地球 而且…\NTotally different from Earth. And yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:43.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要说清楚 并不是与地球完全不一样  只是地球有点超常 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I should be careful, not totally different from Earth, just Earth on steroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:46.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你问你自己 哇 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you ask yourself, wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.81,0:21:49.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不了解木星上在发生什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If I understood what's going on on Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.20,0:21:51.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球就会是个样板 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth would be  just a piece of cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:22:00.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的奥秘并不局限于它本身 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's mysteries aren't limited to the planet itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.63,0:22:04.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它最迷人的东西围绕着它运行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of its most intriguing elements are circling around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.11,0:22:10.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星有几十个卫星 大的可以看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's got several dozen moons that are big enough to be seen
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.23,0:22:14.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大概还有许许多多太小了  现代技术还无法看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and has probably got a lot more that are too small to be seen with current technology
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.33,0:22:18.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毫无疑问 将来会发现它们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and no doubt in coming years more will be discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.99,0:22:21.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些卫星几乎有着行星般的大小 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the moons almost have the size of some planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.67,0:22:24.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以木星真的有着自己的太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So really Jupiter has its own little solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.50,0:22:28.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多谢它那难以置信的引力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks to its incredible gravitational pull,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.38,0:22:31.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把小行星连同其它太空碎片拉住 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it sucked in asteroids along with other space debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.39,0:22:34.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中大部分是有序的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the most part there is order.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.94,0:22:38.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而有一些轨道飘忽不定的卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there are some erratic moons in orbit around Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.85,0:22:43.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它得对付混乱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's managed chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.04,0:22:47.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你能想象出一连串奔跑者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Can you imagine a bunch of runners
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.73,0:22:50.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着跑道 各自停下而不相撞 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the track, in their lanes, each runner stays and they won't collide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.11,0:22:53.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一种天上的技巧 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's kind of a celestial mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.09,0:23:05.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个卫星把握这自己的魔力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each moon holds its own fascination.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:13.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,四个突出的木星卫星是伽利略发现的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Four of Jupiter's prominent moons were discovered by Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.14,0:23:17.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他首次看到它们围绕着木星运转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He first observed that they revolved around the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:22.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们根据木星都被以上帝的情人来命名 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are named for Jupiter, the god's lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.65,0:23:30.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你第一个来到的主要的卫星是爱莪(木卫一) \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first major moon you come into is Io,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.65,0:23:35.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是个非常活跃的地方 有着大量的火山 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is this very active place. There are lots of volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.92,0:23:37.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎随时都在喷发 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's almost all the time going off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.03,0:23:41.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷出200英里的岩浆进入太空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shooting out magma 200 miles into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.82,0:23:46.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫一100多座火山是个奇迹 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Io is a wonder pop-mark with over a hundred volcanoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.90,0:23:51.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些加利福尼亚大小的火山似乎时开时关 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some the size of California which seem to turn themselves on and off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.71,0:23:59.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽尼墨德(木卫三)是太阳系里最大的卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ganymede is the largest moon in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.31,0:24:05.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有地球卫星月亮五倍这么大  卡莉斯托(木卫四)有着最沉重的撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Five times the size of Earth's Moon. Callisto is the most heavily cratered.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.20,0:24:10.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它的生命周期里 明显地遭受了打击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has clearly taken a beating in its lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.38,0:24:15.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着是欧罗巴(木卫二) 木星国王的冰王后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then there is Europa, the ice queen to Jupiter's king.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.75,0:24:18.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没人确切地了解其构造 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one knows its make-up for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.77,0:24:20.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它看上去象个破碎的鸡蛋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It looks like a cracked egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.64,0:24:22.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它真的好象上面整个环绕着水 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It really looks like the whole thing had looped
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.72,0:24:25.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时结冰 有时破裂 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}water on it sometime it froze and it cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.63,0:24:30.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为那种现象是潮汐的力量在破碎 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we believe that these patterns are due to tidal forces that crack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.28,0:24:39.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫二与众不同的是似乎一些地方是平滑的  其它地方是丘陵 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As alien as Europa seems it is smooth and glassy in some spots, hilly in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上它与地球上的一个冰冻世界相似 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact it is remarkably similar to one of Earth's frozen wonderlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.11,0:24:51.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极有个湖叫做东方号 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a lake in Antarctica called lake Vostok that scientists think is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:54.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为与木卫二看到的相似 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an analogy to what we see on Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.17,0:25:01.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极有着厚重的冰盖 下面是液态的湖 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Antarctica has a huge thick ice crust and underneath there is this liquid lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.62,0:25:05.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为与木卫二上看到的可能非常相似 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we think this may be very similar to the water ice underneath the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.85,0:25:07.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰盖下有水 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we see on Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.41,0:25:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你到外壳下面可能得到冰 甚至水 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you go down through the crust you got to the ice and then if you get
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.00,0:25:16.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们非常相信下面会有液态水 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}liquid water. And we are very convinced that there's liquid water down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.24,0:25:18.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是我们已知的地球以外存在水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the only place that we know, beside the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.41,0:25:22.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和大量水的附着体的唯一的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has liquid water and large bodies that have been there, we believe
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.11,0:25:24.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为已经存在了一百万或两百万年了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for more than a million or two million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.19,0:25:31.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那 有水的地方会有生命吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And where there's water, could there be life?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.29,0:25:44.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的卫星木卫二充满了秘密 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's moon Europa is bursting with secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.63,0:25:49.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至可能在其冰壳的下面深处隐藏着温暖的热喷口 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It may even have warm thermal vents deep below its frozen crust.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.87,0:25:56.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 那有个比太平洋更大的广阔的海洋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact there's an immense ocean that's bigger than the Pacific Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.74,0:25:58.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一半的水在那里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}worth half liquid water down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.75,0:26:00.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里孕育着情况的发生 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is sitting there for things to happen to.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.53,0:26:12.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水的存在意味着一件事 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The presence of water means one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.57,0:26:15.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可能并不孤独 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We may not be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.08,0:26:21.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想去木卫二冰下钓鱼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I wanna go ice-fishing on Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.10,0:26:24.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打个洞潜到水里 瞧瞧四周看有没有东西…\NCut a hole, put a submersible, look around, see if anything…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.04,0:26:28.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有什么游到照相机前 轻轻拍打相机 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anything swims up to the camera and licks the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.40,0:26:30.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我想做的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what I wanna do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.30,0:26:40.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一位科学家就在做这样的垂钓旅行计划 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One scientist is planning just such a fishing trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.99,0:26:51.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个得克萨斯州奥斯汀附近的室外实验室里  希望系于一个小机器人身上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this outdoor lab, near Austin, Texas, hopes are hanging on a little robot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.40,0:26:54.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被设计用于未知的地方探险 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is designed for exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.21,0:26:57.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全未知的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in unknown territory, completely unknown territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.89,0:26:59.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,搜索生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and search for biological live.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.89,0:27:06.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是深井热量探测器 简称"DepthX" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a DEep Phreatic THermal eXplorer, or "DepthX" for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.43,0:27:10.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它现在所处的场所是当地的一个采石场 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its proving ground right now is a local quarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.30,0:27:15.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对它的将来有个很大的计划 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are big plans for its future.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.68,0:27:20.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果一切按照计划执行  我们将在2017年进行发射 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If everything went according the plan we would launch around 2017.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.08,0:27:22.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会在2018年抵达木卫二…\NIt would be at Europa by 2018…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.65,0:27:26.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2019年的某个时候  我们将会知道地球外是否存在生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and by 2019 for certain we'll know whether there's life off Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.48,0:27:29.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个赌博 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.91,0:27:35.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深井热量探测器是工程师比尔·斯通的创作 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DepthX is the brainchild of engineer Bill Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.81,0:27:39.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他和一组科学家已经将他们的声誉和它绑在了一起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He and a team of scientists have staked their reputations on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.17,0:27:44.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们化了6年时间来做研发和建立模型 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They spent 6 years developing the concept and building the prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.10,0:27:50.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是雄心勃勃计划的一部分  将看着它被带进太空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's part of an ambitious project that would see it carried into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.32,0:27:54.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过6英里的冰进到木卫二的海洋里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sent through 6 miles of ice and into Europa's ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.45,0:28:04.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被分离下降成为不一样的航天器 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To divide it down into all the various vehicle, you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.71,0:28:09.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母船在绕木卫二的轨道上运行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a parent vehicle which takes you to orbit around the moon Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.51,0:28:17.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能有个登陆车…\NThere would be a lander…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.06,0:28:20.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会登陆在冰上的陆地上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would land on the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.84,0:28:24.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着登陆车进入第二阶段 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then there's a second stage of the lander which melts its way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.37,0:28:29.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,融化3到5公里厚的冰盖 此时进入第三阶段 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from 3 to 5 kilometers of ice cap and then at that point you kick out the 3rd stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.80,0:28:38.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要一个快速移动的装置 就象鱼雷一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We need a fast moving device, that would be sort of torpedo-shaped,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.50,0:28:41.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很有可能是核动力的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most likely nuclear propelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.47,0:28:46.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将围绕木卫二中央海洋行进几千公里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that would drive for thousands of kilometers around the central ocean of Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.10,0:28:55.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这真的可行吗？美国航天局认为可行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is that really feasible? NASA thinks so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.84,0:28:59.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个航天器装载着金钱和祝福 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The space agency is onboard with the money and its blessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.65,0:29:02.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一项搜索生命的投资 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an investment in the search for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.95,0:29:13.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果生命存在于木星的卫星木卫二上  那么它们会走路 说话或飞翔吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If life exists on Jupiter's moon Europa, could it walk, talk or fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.03,0:29:20.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会不会是小细菌 会是最好的细菌？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be little viruses or no, maybe a best bacteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.14,0:29:24.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只能期待看到原始的生命形式 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would expect only to see primitive life forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.83,0:29:28.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但可能是我们在地球上看到过的  我们只是不知道而已 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they might be some more else that we see on Earth, we just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.27,0:29:35.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球最不适合居住的地方发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists are encouraged by the discovering of strange and hardy lifeforms
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.88,0:29:39.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,陌生勇敢的生命形式鼓舞着科学家 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}found in the most inhospitable places on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.32,0:29:42.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如 两种蠕虫 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Two worms, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.96,0:29:45.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在完全黑暗的地方生存繁衍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}survive and thrive in total darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.91,0:29:48.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极端的压力不成问题 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Extreme pressure isn't a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.69,0:29:51.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些生物在1977年被发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The creatures were discovered in 1977
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.83,0:29:55.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在加拉帕戈斯裂谷以下几英里的地方发现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}several miles below the surface of the Galapagos rift.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.72,0:30:00.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们生存在水里 高温喷口的附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They exist in water, near superheated thermal vents.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.57,0:30:06.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信这些极端条件 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's believed that these very conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.24,0:30:09.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑暗 高压和高温 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}darkness, high pressure and hydrothermal vents,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.26,0:30:11.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就存在在木卫二上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are present on Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.93,0:30:17.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果在木卫二地核下和附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you could have hydrothermal vents
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.73,0:30:20.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够发现喷口\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}kicking out warmth and nutrients
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.54,0:30:23.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷出热和养分 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}down and near the core of Europa,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.30,0:30:26.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就能哺育生物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and organisms would have fed off of that material
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.75,0:30:30.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就象早期的地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just likely might have in the early Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.30,0:30:36.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然两个蠕虫不可能隐藏在木卫二的冰盖下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And while two worms might not be lurking beneath Europa's icy shell,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.69,0:30:39.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但至少会有东西的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something else could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:47.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种微生物是地球上的大量的生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This microbial life is the bulk of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.70,0:30:52.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们期待这些生命的分枝会存在于木卫二上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We expect that branches of that type of life would exists on Europa,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.59,0:30:56.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是因为水是其中的关键 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just simply because water is the key feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.80,0:30:59.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找生命折磨着科学家比尔·斯通 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding it consumes scientist Bill Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.99,0:31:04.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深井热量探测器可能是揭开知识奥秘的答案 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its DepthX may answer a question that excites secrets of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.70,0:31:11.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有机器人寻找\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we have the robot behavior look for
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.04,0:31:13.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命的痕迹 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}signs of life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.39,0:31:16.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着搜集找到的样本 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then try to collect the samples based of what it's sensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.27,0:31:20.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,斯通的婴儿还处于幼年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stone's baby is in its infancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.66,0:31:24.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时它也是超前的 高级的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the same time it is futuristic and advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.12,0:31:26.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是高科技的玩具 不象其它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a high tech toy like no other,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.94,0:31:31.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以显示我们世界另外的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that might show our world what another is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.55,0:31:44.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们第一次接触地外生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our first contact with extraterrestrial life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.43,0:31:47.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能在木星的卫星木卫二上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be on Jupiter's moon, Europa.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.36,0:31:56.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深井热量探测器更准确地叫法"水下机器人" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The DepthX robot, or more accurately "Hydrobot",
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.97,0:32:00.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,设计成会自己思考 行动和探索 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is being designed to ultimately think, move and explore
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.86,0:32:03.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而不需要人的帮助 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without help from man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.17,0:32:10.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全靠机器人自己做到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that is all to be done by the robot itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.00,0:32:13.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将不会遥控它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're not gonna be guiding it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.10,0:32:17.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个将要做的大的步骤  我们会称之为机器人科学自治 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's gonna be a big step forward in what we would call robot science autonomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.98,0:32:20.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个人间地狱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a real life hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.89,0:32:23.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个新的太空奥德赛的开始 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The start of a new "Space Odyssey".
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:26.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在底部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're literally
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.52,0:32:28.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,边缘逐个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the bottom edge
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.29,0:32:31.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,分类察看 会重复察看 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}let the type look surface and we won't see it again
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.02,0:32:33.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到告诉了我们下面有什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until it tell us what's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.44,0:32:39.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深潜水热探险者在海洋里航行时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DepthX would be able to extract and analyze samples
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.03,0:32:41.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够自己提取分析样本 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on its own as it navigates the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.94,0:32:48.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们看到的下部伸出的管子会采集水样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This outer tube we see down here  is where we pull in water samples
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.40,0:32:52.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并储存在后面的袋子里  车上装有五个这样的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and store them in one later bag,  we have five of them on-board.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.48,0:32:53.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而早做之前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But before it does that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.78,0:32:57.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上通过左边的微型泵连续工作 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it actually powers through a series of micro pumps here on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.69,0:33:00.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把水带到随车的显微镜下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and brings it into and on-board microscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.56,0:33:04.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显微镜将摄取图象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that microscope will take images
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.09,0:33:06.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到水里5微米左右的物体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what's in the water down to about five microns.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.85,0:33:10.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们几乎能够看到典型的微生物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we can see most of the typical types of microbial life,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.81,0:33:13.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在屏幕上看到从5微米到200微米的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from five to two hundred microns, on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.62,0:33:18.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有生命的话 机器人用这来分别测定 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The robot will use that to discriminate to determine if there is life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.46,0:33:20.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着提取样本 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then grab a sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.48,0:33:27.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深潜水热探险者及其系统必须做得较小便于太空活动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}DepthX and its systems must be made smaller to work in space
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.88,0:33:32.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还必须通过浮冰的考验 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it still must pass trials under ice floes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.03,0:33:35.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在南极测试它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are testing this in Antarctica
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.19,0:33:37.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全能在冰下可靠工作 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to make sure all works totally under ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.92,0:33:44.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木卫二上的生命可能是未知的大餐 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The question of life on Europa is probably the big meal***unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.19,0:33:47.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,主要是它可能会改变我们对宇宙的认识 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because that would change our view of the Universe, basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.05,0:33:49.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是指 如果这个小卫星在那里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean, if this little moon sitting out there
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.77,0:33:51.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在木星恶劣的环境下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in his hostile environment of Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.78,0:33:53.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够有生命存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can have life form on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.99,0:33:56.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就意味着或许会告诉我们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that means that probably tell us that,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.57,0:33:58.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命几乎到处存在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that life is almost everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.70,0:34:01.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在痕迹 我是说 认为搜索生命是一件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sign is there, I mean, I think searching for like is one of the most
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.86,0:34:03.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最引人瞩目的事情 我们能够做的..\Ncompelling things that we can do as…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.69,0:34:07.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅仅是科学家做的 而且还是种族…就象人类做的 \Nas not only as scientist but as a race… as human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.52,0:34:13.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个巨大的引导 不仅仅是对人类 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a giant lead, and not just for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.17,0:34:16.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也不是对机器人族 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nor for robot kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.78,0:34:23.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在所有木星壮丽的映像里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of all Jupiter's imposing features,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.57,0:34:27.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有一个比你无法看到的更让人映像深刻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}none is more impressive than the one you cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.47,0:34:30.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它远比大红斑大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's bigger by far than the Great Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.61,0:34:33.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比气流喷射更具活力 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more dynamic than the bands of jet streams,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.32,0:34:36.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以媲美人们了解的任何杀手 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as lethal as any killer known to men.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.68,0:34:42.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个太阳系里最强烈的辐射环境 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have one of the most powerful radiation environment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.26,0:34:44.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还包括太阳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the solar system, beside from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.54,0:34:48.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为木星的磁场是太阳系里最大的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field of Jupiter is the largest entity, I believe, in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.12,0:34:54.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是个4.5亿英里长泡沫 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is a bubble, 450 million miles long
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.29,0:34:57.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充满电荷粒子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}buzzing with electrically charged particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.30,0:35:00.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是木星的磁气圈 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's Jupiter's magnetosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.94,0:35:13.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳把太阳风送到这里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's sitting here putting out the solar wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.12,0:35:15.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳风充满了质子和电子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the solar wind is charged particle of protons and electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.16,0:35:21.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些粒子流以每小时1英里的速度前进 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These particles flow along at 1 million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.98,0:35:25.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星基本上捕捉到了这些质子和电子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Jupiter basically capture these sort of protons and electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.23,0:35:27.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些粒子是电流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All these charged particles are electrical current
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.48,0:35:31.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且环绕着木星流动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is has it then in the space circling around Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.33,0:35:37.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,英语中没有一个词汇能够准确地表达这种环境的恶劣 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No word in the english language accurately conveys the enormity of this phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.73,0:35:42.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的磁气圈是太阳系里最大的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetosphere of Jupiter is the biggest object is the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.04,0:35:43.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要比太阳大得多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is a lot bigger than the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.19,0:36:01.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对它最好的比喻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Comparisons are the best measure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.12,0:36:03.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是魔力无边的奇迹 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of this mega-mighty-wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.89,0:36:07.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果在夜空显现 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it were visible in the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.74,0:36:11.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会比月亮大许多许多倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be many, many times bigger than the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.50,0:36:13.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是个巨大的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's enormous. Even though
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.36,0:36:17.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管它距离地球是太阳距离地球的五倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's five times as far away from Earth as the Sun is,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.64,0:36:22.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们仍然可以在夜晚看到它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it still would look immense in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.83,0:36:28.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果看到的话 它会以惯常的面孔出现:风向袋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If visible it would take a familiar form: a windsock.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.34,0:36:34.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一个完美的面孔以一个方向对着地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a rounded section facing away from the planet, in one direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.28,0:36:37.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拖着长长的尾巴 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a tail flowing out the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.62,0:36:43.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个风向袋的延伸到土星的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This windsock reaches the outer orbit of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.89,0:36:50.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星产生着1000万安培的电流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Power plant Jupiter generates up to ten million amps of electrical current.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.06,0:36:53.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个太阳系里最大的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The biggest planet in the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.96,0:36:57.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以操控所有经过它周围的电流 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can conduct electricity all the way through and around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.12,0:37:08.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这产生了我们能够看到的一种现象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This conductivity creates a phenomenon we can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.26,0:37:12.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时激发了带电粒子逃逸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the excited charged particles escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.61,0:37:15.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星有极光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter has auroras,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.16,0:37:21.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为在这些粒子进入大气层的时候会发光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because when those particles leak in and crash into the upper atmosphere, it glows.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.82,0:37:24.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就象地球的极光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as Earth has auroras.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.77,0:37:36.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些可怕的极光要1000倍地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These ghostly auroras are a thousand times more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.43,0:37:38.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强于地球南极和北极的极光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than Earth's northern and southern lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.26,0:37:42.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们处在1200英里高空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They measure up to 1,200 miles across.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.98,0:37:46.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在它们下面看的话 它们弥漫着整个天空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you could stand under them, they'd fill the entire sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.98,0:37:51.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以每小时一万英里闪电般的速度移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving at lightning speed, ten thousand miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.93,0:37:55.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星的磁场是个嚎叫着的怪物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter's magnetic field is a monster and it roars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.11,0:37:59.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上是在对我们演讲 就在现在 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact it's speaking to us, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.17,0:38:08.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星…\NJupiter…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.67,0:38:14.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系里的巨人在向我们说着什么  如果你注意听的话 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The giant of the solar system has something to say, if you're listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.87,0:38:17.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够听到的称为"狮吼" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can hear what we call "lion roars",
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.81,0:38:19.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为它是咆哮的声音 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}'cause it has this roaring sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.72,0:38:23.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够听到吹口哨的声音 听到嘘声…\NWe can hear whistler modes, we can hear hiss…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.59,0:38:28.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,口哨是这样形成的:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And whistles that are going:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.95,0:38:32.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是动力学的原理 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these are all indications of dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.94,0:38:35.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体在磁气圈里产生的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}things that are happening in the magnetosphere now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.61,0:38:41.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你发现自己在昏暗的沙漠高速公路上行驶 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you find yourself driving on a dark desert highway,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.05,0:38:48.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,车上的无线电刚好调到木星磁气圈发出的声音 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}your AM radio might just tune in to the strange sounds of Jupiter's magnetosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.52,0:38:58.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,脉冲短则几秒 长则几分钟 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The bursts are as short as a few seconds, and as long as a couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.34,0:39:01.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每时每刻变化不断 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They come and go every hour too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:07.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分声音就象静电  但是每次都是在你拿起东西的时候 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of it sounds like static, but every once in a while you pick up something
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.30,0:39:10.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,声音就象拿起或放下石头 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sounds like a rising tone or a falling tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.26,0:39:22.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听众形容无线电的声音象啄木鸟 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sound listeners have described audio spasms that sound like woodpeckers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.38,0:39:27.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者象海浪冲刷着海滩 噪音真的很烦 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or waves crashing on the beach. The noise is disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.64,0:39:51.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而这就是行星的演讲 保持的一个谜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But just why the planet was talking, remained a mystery until Voyager II
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.62,0:39:55.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到1979年航海者2号经过磁气圈的外层后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}passed through the outer magnetosphere, in 1979.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.71,0:40:06.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长期以来 没人真正明白那些信号是如何产生的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nobody really understood for a long time how those signals were generated.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.28,0:40:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以那是我对木星感兴趣时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that was one of those things that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.94,0:40:13.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关注的一个情况 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was on my mind when I got interested in Jupiter. What in the world was going on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.23,0:40:16.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些无线电喷发究竟是什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with these radio emissions?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.68,0:40:26.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是木星最终要被解开的一个迷团 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is one of the few secrets finally surrendered by Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.51,0:40:34.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然解答了一些问题 但新的问题又凸现出来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that answered some questions but it raised new ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.95,0:40:38.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个…我想这是个途径 如果你没有问题 \NAnd… I think that's the way it should be. If you don't have questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.75,0:40:41.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是讨厌的忍耐 所以…\Nit gets kind of boring endures. So…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.44,0:40:45.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想事实上行星不可能轻易地被揭开秘密 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think that the fact that the planets don't give up their secrets easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.50,0:40:50.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者宇宙不可能 这是游戏的一部分  这就是让人感兴趣的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or the Universe doesn't, that's part of the game, it's what it makes it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.87,0:40:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星继续迷惑着科学家 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter keeps astounding and confounding scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.09,0:41:06.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个惊奇来自1979年 当时发现木星有个环 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One surprise came in 1979, when it was discovered that Jupiter has a ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.86,0:41:14.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对土星没什么 但却是另外一个迷人的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's nothing on the order of Saturn's, still, it's another feature that fascinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.12,0:41:18.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有的大行星都有环 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of the giant planets have rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.56,0:41:23.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许是来自行星形成时的残余物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}probably leftover from when the planets formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.53,0:41:28.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卫星在气体外凝结 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the moons coagulated out of the gas that was there and then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.31,0:41:30.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这可能是没有成功的卫星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it could be a failed moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.82,0:41:34.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以木星的环来自一个内部的卫星的碎片 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, Jupiter's ring comes from material being knocked off
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.47,0:41:42.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它收集了来自来自外面的卫星的尘埃 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of one of the interior moons. So its dust is collected from material that's coming in from outside moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.21,0:41:48.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着新的物质进入 环慢慢地长大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ring is slowly growing as new material flows into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.27,0:41:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且这个行星的另一面还是一个谜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there's a whole other side of the planet that remains a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.44,0:41:59.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么这个风暴斑能够保持 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why do the storm spots keep forming.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.66,0:42:02.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如 有一个暗斑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's the Dark Spot, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.93,0:42:06.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在1997年被首次看到 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Glimpses of it were first spied in 1997.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.61,0:42:11.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是地球两倍大的巨大云团 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It appeared to be a huge ominous cloud twice the size of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.32,0:42:14.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,盘旋在木星败绩上空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hovering above Jupiter's North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.29,0:42:18.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有许多其它的斑点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a host of other spots too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.36,0:42:22.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有其它小的来来往往 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are other sort of smaller cousins that have come and gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.91,0:42:27.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有红斑三分之二大小的三个卵状物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there were three ovals about half a third of the size of the Red Spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.67,0:42:33.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们占据着相同的纬度 结束在大气层的南方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they used to occupy the same latitude end in the southern atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.17,0:42:35.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们自1930年以来就一直在运行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they've been around since the 1930's.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.32,0:42:43.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及…业余天文家说发现至少在90年代还在运行 \NAnd… amateur astronomers saw them formed and they were around till the late 90's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.33,0:42:48.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且其中的两个已经合并 接着还有两个也合并了 \Nand they… two of them merged with each other, and then the remaining two merged,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.68,0:42:50.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在只有一个了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now there's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.36,0:42:52.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它继续在变形 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it keeps transforming.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.92,0:42:54.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在6个月前围绕着红斑运行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have turned to red about six months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.92,0:42:56.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它被称为小红斑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's now call it the Little Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.82,0:43:00.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它会改变颜色 而为什么会改变颜色是个谜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it turned color and why did they turn color is a big question.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.07,0:43:02.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,化学或某种矢量动力学在继续 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's chemistry going on, or some type of vector dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.65,0:43:06.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要开始研究 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is going out it just kicked in and we need to start studying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.80,0:43:13.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星是不怀好意的 不安宁的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter is a hostile and restless planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.60,0:43:16.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它那气态身躯和强烈的风暴 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its giant gaseous body and violent storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.79,0:43:20.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了太阳系里最不一样的环境 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}make it one of the most alien environments in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.64,0:43:23.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使它距离我们有5亿英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though it is half a billion miles from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.54,0:43:27.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是与我们要比我们想象的有更多的共同点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we may have more in common with our cousin planet than we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.48,0:43:34.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为从木星学习的是…\NI think the lesson to learn from Jupiter here is…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.50,0:43:38.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论我们的气候和气象模式怎样变化 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whatever's going on in our climate and our weather patterns here on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.02,0:43:41.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星要厉害的多 但是地球不是个安全岛 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Jupiter has more of it, but Earth is not an island,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.25,0:43:46.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上发生的最好的例子甚至要比地球本身来得好 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they're better examples of what 's going on on Earth than even Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.27,0:43:52.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,木星是关于我们太阳系许多问题的关键 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For scientists, Jupiter is the king of many questions concerning our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.24,0:43:55.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家可能会掌握它的答案 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and could possibly hold the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.80,0:44:08.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
